  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in the pressure cooker on sauté mode. Add the onion, garlic, and chopped chili; cook until the onion softens, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add the sliced bell peppers, oregano, smoked paprika, cayenne, salt, and black pepper. Sauté for another 2 minutes to release the peppers' aroma.",
    "Pour in the vegetable broth and a splash of lemon juice. Seal the lid and cook at high pressure for 10 minutes.",
    "Quickly release the pressure, stir the stew, then fold in the Greek yogurt until the mixture is smooth and creamy.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning if needed. Sprinkle crumbled feta over the top before serving."
